{"insight":"Practice needs a trusted mirror","publicTitle":"Who Names the Change","plainSummary":"A practice can guide a person, but trusted people help name what changed and what still needs care.","atAGlance":"After deep practice, the hard question is who can help us understand the change. A quiet mind can still misread itself. Some people need wise companions, and some need distance from false voices. The test is whether the practice leaves us more honest, steady, and open to correction.","keyPoints":["Meaning grows clearer when trusted people can hear the change without owning it.","Alone, a seeker may confuse calm, fear, and insight.","Test whether guidance makes life more honest, steady, and kind."],"match":["a practice cannot name itself"],"tags":["practice","trust","community"]}
